('Read this passage: "The Amazon rainforest is home to millions of species of plants and animals. Scientists estimate that many species living there have not yet been discovered. The rainforest produces about 20% of the world''s oxygen and absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere." What evidence supports that the Amazon is important to Earth?', 'essay', 'reading', 'Grade 4', 'us', '[]', '', 'Students should identify: produces 20% oxygen, absorbs CO2, supports biodiversity. Look for text evidence.', 4, 4),
('Which word is a synonym for "enormous"?', 'multiple_choice', 'reading', 'Grade 4', 'us', '["tiny", "huge", "medium", "colorful"]', 'huge', 'Enormous and huge both mean very large in size.', 3, 1),
('A rectangular playground is 45 feet long and 30 feet wide. What is the area of the playground in square feet?', 'short_answer', 'math', 'Grade 4', 'us', '[]', '1,350 square feet', 'Area = length √ó width = 45 √ó 30 = 1,350 square feet.', 3, 2),

